Class CopyPasteManagerEx

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.ide.CopyPasteManager
      • com.intellij.ide.CopyPasteManagerEx
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.datatransfer.ClipboardOwner

    public class CopyPasteManagerEx
extends CopyPasteManager
implements java.awt.datatransfer.ClipboardOwner
    This implementation attempts to limit memory occupied by clipboard history. To make it work, Transferable instances passed to setContents(Transferable) should implement Sizeable interface. See getSize(Transferable) method for details on estimating the size of Transferable and deleteAfterAllowedMaximum() method for history trimming logic.

      • stopKillRings

        public void stopKillRings()
        Description copied from class: CopyPasteManager
        We support 'kill rings' at the editor, i.e. every time when subsequent adjacent regions of text are copied they are combined into single compound region. Every non-adjacent change makes existing regions unable to combine.

        However, there are situations when all 'kill rings' should be stopped manually (e.g. on undo). Hence, we need a handle to ask for that. This method works like such a handle.

        Specified by:
        stopKillRings in class CopyPasteManager
        See Also:
